Function Documentation

int32_t TestFmk_close ( TestFmk_Handle  handle,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to close the TestFmk Module and associated profile. This is only applicable from the TestFmk Instance which has loaded the profile.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the TestFmk Module
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

int32_t TestFmk_execute ( TestFmk_Handle  handle,
TestFmk_Result *  ptrResult,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function executes the TestFmk Module. Execution of the TestFmk module involves the following:-

  • Handling of the reception of the IPC Messages exchanged between the TestFmk Peers.
  • Processing of the ADC data as per the loaded profile.
Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the TestFmk Module
[out]ptrResultPointer to the result populated by the loaded profile.
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
TestFmk_Handle TestFmk_init ( TestFmk_InitCfg *  ptrInitCfg,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to initialize the data path manager and initialize and load the profile.

Parameters

[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- Handle to the TestFmk Module
Error- NULL

int32_t TestFmk_synch ( TestFmk_Handle  fmkHandle,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to synchronize the execution of the framework between the domains.

Parameters
[in]fmkHandleHandle to the framework
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API on an error
Return values
Synchronized- 1
Unsynchronized- 0
Error- <0
